parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch Failure and Electrical Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failure can cause electrical fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
Alternator failure can cause electrical fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: fire requires extended use of a hose to put out

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seat belt latch failure can cause the seat belt to malfunction, which can lead to injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Driver's side seat belt latch no longer locks or latches
webbing is covered with an interior color-matching trim piece
electrical harness runs inside the trim piece and splits halfway through the belt's webbing
potentially weakening the restraint of the seat belt by 50%.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal sinking or failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to stop
smoke or fire from the brakes
the rear anti-lock brakes lock up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause damage to the vehicle, injuries, and even fatalities. They can also lead to costly repairs and potentially result in a total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire while driving
the vehicle's electrical system may malfunction
and there may be a burning smell or noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature wear on engine components, increased emissions, and decreased fuel efficiency. If left unchecked, it can cause engine failure, resulting in costly repairs or even requiring a new engine.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the engine may make unusual noises or produce excessive smoke
and the check engine light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and delamination can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to surrounding vehicles, resulting in potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: delamination of tire tread from the donut

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A spare tire fire can cause damage to the vehicle, surrounding vehicles, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Spare tire caught fire due to proximity to the exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Master Cylinder Reinforcement Plate Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the reinforcement plate on the clutch master cylinder can cause separation from the dash panel, leading to leakage and potential failure of the clutch system, which can result in difficulty shifting gears and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud noise from the transmission can indicate internal damage or wear, potentially leading to transmission failure, which can cause loss of power, difficulty shifting gears, and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the rear axle can cause vibration, noise, and loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: or grinding sounds from the rear axle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle grease seal can cause grease to leak onto the brake shoes, potentially leading to brake failure, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Grease leakage from the rear axle
